InetAddress.description: Denotes a generic Internet address. An InetAddress value is always interpreted within the context of an InetAddressType value. Every usage of the InetAddress textual convention is required to specify the InetAddressType object that provides the context. It is suggested that the InetAddressType object be logically registered before the object(s) that use the InetAddress textual convention, if they appear in the same logical row. The value of an InetAddress object must always be consistent with the value of the associated InetAddressType object. Attempts to set an InetAddress object to a value inconsistent with the associated InetAddressType must fail with an inconsistentValue error. When this textual convention is used as the syntax of an index object, there may be issues with the limit of 128 sub-identifiers specified in SMIv2, STD 58. In this case, the object definition MUST include a 'SIZE' clause to limit the number of potential instance sub-identifiers; otherwise the applicable constraints MUST be stated in the appropriate conceptual row DESCRIPTION clauses, or in the surrounding documentation if there is no single DESCRIPTION clause that is appropriate.
InetAddress.name: InetAddress

InetAddressPrefixLength.description: Denotes the length of a generic Internet network address prefix. A value of n corresponds to an IP address mask that has n contiguous 1-bits from the most significant bit (MSB), with all other bits set to 0. An InetAddressPrefixLength value is always interpreted within the context of an InetAddressType value. Every usage of the InetAddressPrefixLength textual convention is required to specify the InetAddressType object that provides the context. It is suggested that the InetAddressType object be logically registered before the object(s) that use the InetAddressPrefixLength textual convention, if they appear in the same logical row. InetAddressPrefixLength values larger than the maximum length of an IP address for a specific InetAddressType are treated as the maximum significant value applicable for the InetAddressType. The maximum significant value is 32 for the InetAddressType 'ipv4(1)' and 'ipv4z(3)' and 128 for the InetAddressType 'ipv6(2)' and 'ipv6z(4)'. The maximum significant value for the InetAddressType 'dns(16)' is 0. The value zero is object-specific and must be defined as part of the description of any object that uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where the Internet network address prefix is unknown or does not apply. The upper bound of the prefix length has been chosen to be consistent with the maximum size of an InetAddress.
InetAddressPrefixLength.name: InetAddressPrefixLength

InetAddressType.description: A value that represents a type of Internet address. unknown(0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address that is not in one of the formats defined below. ipv4(1) An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention. ipv6(2) An IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention. ipv4z(3) A non-global IPv4 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv4z textual convention. ipv6z(4) A non-global IPv6 address including a zone index as defined by the InetAddressIPv6z textual convention. dns(16) A DNS domain name as defined by the InetAddressDNS textual convention. Each definition of a concrete InetAddressType value must be accompanied by a definition of a textual convention for use with that InetAddressType. To support future extensions, the InetAddressType textual convention SHOULD NOT be sub-typed in object type definitions. It MAY be sub-typed in compliance statements in order to require only a subset of these address types for a compliant implementation. Implementations must ensure that InetAddressType objects and any dependent objects (e.g., InetAddress objects) are consistent. An inconsistentValue error must be generated if an attempt to change an InetAddressType object would, for example, lead to an undefined InetAddress value. In -- [Page 6] particular, InetAddressType/InetAddress pairs must be changed together if the address type changes (e.g., from ipv6(2) to ipv4(1)).
InetAddressType.name: InetAddressType

hwISIS.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwISIS.description: The HUAWEI PRIVATE MIB contains objects belonging to processes of the IS-IS protocol existing on the system. It defines the model used to represent data that exists elsewhere in the system and on peripheral devices. There are no constraints on this MIB.
hwISIS.name: hwISIS

hwIsisAdjSysID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually.
hwIsisAdjSysID.name: hwIsisAdjSysID

hwIsisAdjSysName.description: Configures the name of the IS-IS dynamic host. The value is a string of 1 to 64 characters. When the length is 0, the configured IS-IS dynamic host name is deleted.
hwIsisAdjSysName.name: hwIsisAdjSysName

hwIsisAutoSysId.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually.
hwIsisAutoSysId.name: hwIsisAutoSysId

hwIsisCircBfdFrrBinding.description: This object indicates that the BFD status is bound to IS-IS Auto FRR. enable(1): indicates that BFD is bound to IS-IS Auto FRR. disable(2): indicates that BFD is not bound to IS-IS Auto FRR. By default, the BFD session status is not bound to IS-IS Auto FRR.
hwIsisCircBfdFrrBinding.name: hwIsisCircBfdFrrBinding

hwIsisCircBfdMinRxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the minimum interval for sending BFD packets. The value range and default value of this object are determined by the license file.
hwIsisCircBfdMinRxInterval.name: hwIsisCircBfdMinRxInterval

hwIsisCircBfdMinTxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the minimum interval for sending BFD packets. The value range and default value of this object are determined by the license file.
hwIsisCircBfdMinTxInterval.name: hwIsisCircBfdMinTxInterval

hwIsisCircBfdMultiplier.description: The value of this object identifies the local BFD detection multiplier. The value range and default value of this object are determined by the license file.
hwIsisCircBfdMultiplier.name: hwIsisCircBfdMultiplier

hwIsisCircBfdState.description: The value of this object identifies the BFD status: enable(1): enables BFD. disable(2): disables BFD. static(3): configures static BFD. block(4): blocks BFD on an interface. By default, BFD is not enabled.
hwIsisCircBfdState.name: hwIsisCircBfdState

hwIsisCircDisName.description: The value of this object identifies the DIS name of an interface. The configuration is applicable to only a broadcast interface. The value is a string of 0 to 64 characters. Value 0 indicates that the DIS name is not configured.
hwIsisCircDisName.name: hwIsisCircDisName

hwIsisCircFrrBackup.description: The value of this object identifies whether an interface is enabled to become a backup interface in Loop Free Alternate (LFA) calculation. Null(0): disables an interface from becoming a backup interface in LFA calculation. level1(1): specifies an interface as a backup interface in Level-1. level2(2): specifies an interface as a backup interface in Level-2. level12(3): specifies an interface as a backup interface in Level-1 and Level-2.
hwIsisCircFrrBackup.name: hwIsisCircFrrBackup

hwIsisCircIpIgnore.description: The value of this object identifies whether the segment in an IP address is checked: enable(1): indicates that the segment in an IP address is not checked. disable(2): indicates that the segment in an IP address is checked. By default, the segment in an IP address is checked. This object applies to only P2P interfaces.
hwIsisCircIpIgnore.name: hwIsisCircIpIgnore

hwIsisCircL1AuthCode.description: The value of this object identifies the authentication code of Level-1 Hello PDUs: none(0): indicates that no authentication is configured. osi(10): indicates OSI authentication. ip(133): indicates IP authentication.
hwIsisCircL1AuthCode.name: hwIsisCircL1AuthCode

hwIsisCircL1AuthKeychainName.description: The value of this object identifies the keychain name of Level-1 Hello packets. The keychain name is a string of characters. The name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that the authentication password of Level-1 Hello packets is not configured. When read, it returns the keychain name.
hwIsisCircL1AuthKeychainName.name: hwIsisCircL1AuthKeychainName

hwIsisCircL1AuthMode.description: The value of this object identifies the mode of authenticating Level-1 Hello PDUs: null(0): indicates that area-based authentication is not configured. md5(1): indicates that the password is encrypted through MD5 and then sent. simple(2): indicates that the password is sent in plaintext. keychain(3): indicates that the key-chain that varies with the time is encrypted through MD5 and then sent. By default, area-based authentication is not configured.
hwIsisCircL1AuthMode.name: hwIsisCircL1AuthMode

hwIsisCircL1AuthSendOnly.description: The value of this object identifies the mode of sending the authentication password of Level-1 Hello PDUs: true(1): indicates that the passwords in only the sent PDUs are authenticated but not in the received PDUs. false(2): indicates that the passwords in both sent and received PDUs are authenticated. By default, the passwords in both sent and received PDUs are authenticated.
hwIsisCircL1AuthSendOnly.name: hwIsisCircL1AuthSendOnly

hwIsisCircL1AuthText.description: The value of this object identifies the authentication password of Level-1 Hello packets. The password is a string of characters. If the packet authentication mode is simple, the password is a string of 0 to 16 characters. If the packet authentication mode is MD5, the password is a string of 0 to 392 characters. If the packet authentication mode is keychain, the name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that the authentication password of Level-1 Hello packets is not configured. When read, it always returns length 0.
hwIsisCircL1AuthText.name: hwIsisCircL1AuthText

hwIsisCircL1Cost.description: The value of this object identifies the Level-1 cost of an interface. If the cost style is wide or widecompatible, the range of this value is from 0 to 16777215, else the range of this value is from 0 to 63. The value of 0 means undo this configuration, and the cost of the circuit will become the default value.
hwIsisCircL1Cost.name: hwIsisCircL1Cost

hwIsisCircL1DisPriority.description: The value of this object identifies the priority of the Level-1 DIS, which is valid only on a broadcast interface. The value ranges from 0 to 127. By default, it is 64.
hwIsisCircL1DisPriority.name: hwIsisCircL1DisPriority

hwIsisCircL1HelloInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for sending Level-1 Hello PDUs. The value ranges from 3 to 255, in seconds. By default, the value is 10s.
hwIsisCircL1HelloInterval.name: hwIsisCircL1HelloInterval

hwIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.description: The value of this object identifies the number of Level-1 Hello PDUs that fail to received from the IS-IS neighbor before the neighbor declared Down. The value ranges from 3 to 1000. By default, the value is 3.
hwIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier.name: hwIsisCircL1HelloMultiplier

hwIsisCircL2AuthCode.description: The value of this object identifies the authentication code of Level-2 Hello PDUs: none(0): indicates that no authentication is configured. osi(10): indicates OSI authentication. ip(133): indicates IP authentication.
hwIsisCircL2AuthCode.name: hwIsisCircL2AuthCode

hwIsisCircL2AuthKeychainName.description: The value of this object identifies the keychain name of Level-2 Hello packets. The keychain name is a string of characters. The name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that the authentication password of Level-2 Hello packets is not configured. When read, it returns the keychain name.
hwIsisCircL2AuthKeychainName.name: hwIsisCircL2AuthKeychainName

hwIsisCircL2AuthMode.description: The value of this object identifies the mode of authenticating Level-2 Hello PDUs: null(0): indicates that area-based authentication is not configured. md5(1): indicates that password is encrypted through MD5 and then sent. simple(2): indicates that the password is sent in plaintext. keychain(3): indicates that the key-chain that varies with the time is encrypted through MD5 and then sent. By default, area-based authentication is not configured.
hwIsisCircL2AuthMode.name: hwIsisCircL2AuthMode

hwIsisCircL2AuthSendOnly.description: The value of this object identifies the mode of sending the authentication password of Level-2 Hello PDUs: true(1): indicates that the passwords in only the sent PDUs are authenticated but not in the received PDUs. false(2): indicates that the password is authenticated in the PDUs that are both sent and received. By default, the passwords in both sent and received PDUs are authenticated.
hwIsisCircL2AuthSendOnly.name: hwIsisCircL2AuthSendOnly

hwIsisCircL2AuthText.description: The value of this object identifies the authentication password of Level-2 Hello packets. The password is a string of characters. If the packet authentication mode is simple, the password is a string of 0 to 16 characters. If the packet authentication mode is MD5, the password is a string of 0 to 392 characters. If the packet authentication mode is keychain, the name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that the authentication password of Level-2 Hello packets is not configured. When read, it always returns length 0.
hwIsisCircL2AuthText.name: hwIsisCircL2AuthText

hwIsisCircL2Cost.description: The value of this object identifies the Level-2 cost of an interface. If the cost style is wide or widecompatible, the range of this value is from 0 to 16777215, else the range of this value is from 0 to 63. The value of 0 means undo this configuration, and the cost of the circuit will become the default value.
hwIsisCircL2Cost.name: hwIsisCircL2Cost

hwIsisCircL2DisPriority.description: The value of this object identifies the priority of the Level-2 DIS, which is valid only on a broadcast interface. The value ranges from 0 to 127. By default, it is 64.
hwIsisCircL2DisPriority.name: hwIsisCircL2DisPriority

hwIsisCircL2HelloInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for sending Level-2 Hello PDUs. The value ranges from 3 to 255, in seconds. By default, the value is 10s.
hwIsisCircL2HelloInterval.name: hwIsisCircL2HelloInterval

hwIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.description: The value of this object identifies the number of Level-2 Hello PDUs that fail to received from the IS-IS neighbor before the neighbor declared Down. The value ranges from 3 to 1000. By default, the value is 3.
hwIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier.name: hwIsisCircL2HelloMultiplier

hwIsisCircLdpHldMaxCost.description: The value of this object identifies the timeout period of the Hold-Max-Cost time for synchronization of IS-IS and LDP. The value ranges from 0 to 65536, in seconds. By default, the value is 10s. The value of 65536 means infinite. 0 means to stop Hold-Max-Cost timer. -1 means no configuration.
hwIsisCircLdpHldMaxCost.name: hwIsisCircLdpHldMaxCost

hwIsisCircLdpSync.description: The value of this object identifies the status of synchronization of IS-IS and LDP: enable(1): enables synchronization of IS-IS and LDP. disable(2): disables synchronization of IS-IS and LDP. By default, synchronization of IS-IS and LDP is disabled.
hwIsisCircLdpSync.name: hwIsisCircLdpSync

hwIsisCircLdpSyncHoldDown.description: The value of this object identifies the timeout period of the Holddown time for synchronization of IS-IS and LDP. The value ranges from 0 to 65535, in seconds. By default, the value is 10s. 0 means to stop Holddown timer. -1 means no configuration.
hwIsisCircLdpSyncHoldDown.name: hwIsisCircLdpSyncHoldDown

hwIsisCircLevel.description: The value of this object identifies the level of an interface: level1(1): indicates Level-1. level2(2): indicates Level-2. level12(3): indicates Level-1-2. By default, the interface is at Level-1-2.
hwIsisCircLevel.name: hwIsisCircLevel

hwIsisCircLspRetransInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for resending LSPs. The value ranges from 1 to 300, in seconds. The default value is 5. This object applies to only P2P interfaces.
hwIsisCircLspRetransInterval.name: hwIsisCircLspRetransInterval

hwIsisCircMTRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table: createAndGo(4): indicates that a row is created. destroy(6): indicates that a row is deleted.
hwIsisCircMTRowStatus.name: hwIsisCircMTRowStatus

hwIsisCircMeshBlock.description: The value of this object identifies the mesh block function. If this function is configured, the set mesh-group ID is deleted. The value of this object can be: enable(1): enables the mesh block function. disable(2): disables the mesh block function. By default, the function is disabled.
hwIsisCircMeshBlock.name: hwIsisCircMeshBlock

hwIsisCircMeshGroup.description: The value of this object identifies the mesh-group ID. The value ranges from 0 to 4294967295. Value 0 indicates that the mesh-group ID is not set.
hwIsisCircMeshGroup.name: hwIsisCircMeshGroup

hwIsisCircPadHello.description: The value of this object identifies whether IS-IS sends standard Hello PDUs with the padding field: enable(1): indicates that IS-IS sends standard Hello PDUs with the padding field. disable(2): indicates that IS-IS does not send standard Hello PDUs with the padding field. By default, the function is disabled.
hwIsisCircPadHello.name: hwIsisCircPadHello

hwIsisCircPppNego.description: The value of this object identifies the mode of negotiating the setup of a neighbor relationship on P2P interfaces: none(0): indicates that the negotiation mode used to establish a neighbor relationship is not specified. twoWay(1): indicates that a neighbor relationship is set up through negotiations in two-way handshake mode. threeWay(2): indicates that a neighbor relationship is set up through negotiations in three-way handshake mode. threeWayOnly(3): indicates that a neighbor relationship is set up through negotiations in three-way handshake mode and the backward compatibility is not supported. By default, a neighbor relationship is set up through negotiations in three-way handshake mode.
hwIsisCircPppNego.name: hwIsisCircPppNego

hwIsisCircPppOsicpCheck.description: The value of this object identifies whether the OSICP check is required: enable(1): enables the OSICP check. disable(2): disables the OSICP check. By default, the function is disabled. This object applies to only P2P interfaces.
hwIsisCircPppOsicpCheck.name: hwIsisCircPppOsicpCheck

hwIsisCircSenseRpr.description: The value of this object identifies whether fast RPR loop detection is enabled: enable(1): enables fast RPR loop detection. disable(2): disables fast RPR loop detection. By default, fast RPR loop detection is disabled.
hwIsisCircSenseRpr.name: hwIsisCircSenseRpr

hwIsisCircSilent.description: The value of this object identifies whether the status of an IS-IS interface is set to silent. enable(1): indicates that the status of IS-IS interface is set to silent. disable(2): indicates that the status of IS-IS interface is not set to silent. By default, the function is disabled.
hwIsisCircSilent.name: hwIsisCircSilent

hwIsisCircSimulation.description: The value of this object identifies whether the broadcast interface is simulated as a P2P interface: enable(1): indicates that the broadcast interface is simulated as a P2P interface. disable(2): indicates that the broadcast interface is not simulated as a P2P interface. By default, broadcast interfaces are not simulated as P2P interfaces.
hwIsisCircSimulation.name: hwIsisCircSimulation

hwIsisCircSmallHello.description: The value of this object identifies whether IS-IS sends small Hello PDUs without the padding field: enable(1): indicates that IS-IS sends small Hello PDUs without the padding field. disable(2): indicates that IS-IS does not send small Hello PDUs without the padding field. By default, the function is disabled.
hwIsisCircSmallHello.name: hwIsisCircSmallHello

hwIsisCircStrictSnpaCheckEnable.description: The value of this object identifies whether the snpa check of lsp and snp is required. enable(1): enables the snpa check. disable(2): disables the snpa check. By default, the function is disabled. This object applies to only simulated P2P interfaces.
hwIsisCircStrictSnpaCheckEnable.name: hwIsisCircStrictSnpaCheckEnable

hwIsisCircSuppReachablity.description: The value of this object identifies whether the advertisement of the interface address is suppressed: Null(0): indicates that the interface address can be advertised. level1(1): indicates that the advertisement of the Level-1 interface address is suppressed. level2(2): indicates that the advertisement of the Level-2 interface address is suppressed. level12(3): indicates that the advertisement of the Level-1 and Level-2 interface addresses is suppressed. By default, the interface address can be advertised.
hwIsisCircSuppReachablity.name: hwIsisCircSuppReachablity

hwIsisConflictSystemID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually.
hwIsisConflictSystemID.name: hwIsisConflictSystemID

hwIsisEnableIPProtocol.description: The value of this object identifies the status of IPv4 IS-IS on an interface: enable(1): enables IPv4 IS-IS. disable(2): disables IPv4 IS-IS.
hwIsisEnableIPProtocol.name: hwIsisEnableIPProtocol

hwIsisEnableIPv6Protocol.description: The value of this object identifies the status of IPv6 IS-IS on an interface: enable(1): enables IPv6 IS-IS. disable(2): disables IPv6 IS-IS.
hwIsisEnableIPv6Protocol.name: hwIsisEnableIPv6Protocol

hwIsisFrrEnabled.description: The value of this object identifies the status of FRR: enable(1): enables FRR. disable(2): disables FRR. By default, FRR is disabled.
hwIsisFrrEnabled.name: hwIsisFrrEnabled

hwIsisFrrEntry.description: Entry of frr commands for the specific MT of process.
hwIsisFrrEntry.name: hwIsisFrrEntry

hwIsisFrrLoopFreeAltLevel.description: The value of this object identifies the level of the FRR LFA algorithm. null(0): cancels the operation of the LFA algorithm. level1(1): indicates Level-1. level2(2): indicates Level-2. level12(3): indicates Level-1-2.
hwIsisFrrLoopFreeAltLevel.name: hwIsisFrrLoopFreeAltLevel

hwIsisFrrPolicyName.description: The value of this object identifies the FRR policy name. The value is a string of 1 to 40 characters. Value 0 indicates that the FRR policy is deleted.
hwIsisFrrPolicyName.name: hwIsisFrrPolicyName

hwIsisImportCost.description: Cost of the imported routes. If the costStyle of the process is wide or widecompatible, the range of this value is from 0 to 4261412864, else the range of this value is from 0 to 63. 0 means no configuration.
hwIsisImportCost.name: hwIsisImportCost

hwIsisImportCostType.description: This object indicates the cost type of the imported external route. This object does not apply to IPv6. internal(1): indicates internal. external(2): indicates external. This node is invalid for IPv6. By default, the cost type of the imported external route is external.
hwIsisImportCostType.name: hwIsisImportCostType

hwIsisImportInheritCostEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the original cost of the source route is inherited: true(1): indicates that the original cost of the source route is inherited. false(2): indicates that the original cost of the source route is not inherited.
hwIsisImportInheritCostEnabled.name: hwIsisImportInheritCostEnabled

hwIsisImportLevel.description: This object indicates the local IS-IS level of the imported route: level1(1): indicates Level-1. level2(2): indicates Level-2. level12(3): indicates Level-1-2.
hwIsisImportLevel.name: hwIsisImportLevel

hwIsisImportPolicyName.description: This object indicates the name of the routing policy used to import routes. The name is a string of 0 to 40 characters. The length 0 indicates that no name is configured for the routing policy used to import routes.
hwIsisImportPolicyName.name: hwIsisImportPolicyName

hwIsisImportProcessIdIndex.description: Process ID of the route protocols. The range is from 1 to 65535. If the protocol is direct, static or bgp, this value can only be 1.
hwIsisImportProcessIdIndex.name: hwIsisImportProcessIdIndex

hwIsisImportProtocolIndex.description: This object indicates the routing protocol of the imported routes: direct(1): indicates direct. static(2): indicates static. rip(3): indicates RIP. ospf(4): indicates OSPF isis(5): indicates IS-IS. bgp(6): For VPN instance, indicates EBGP and IBGP, otherwise indicates EBGP. ospfv3(7): indicates OSPFv3. ripng(8): indicates RIPng. bgpIbgp(9): For VPN instance, this is unusable, otherwise indicates IBGP and EBGP.
hwIsisImportProtocolIndex.name: hwIsisImportProtocolIndex

hwIsisImportRouteStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table: createAndGo(4): indicates that a row is created. destroy(6): indicates that a row is deleted.
hwIsisImportRouteStatus.name: hwIsisImportRouteStatus

hwIsisImportTag.description: This object indicates the administrative tag assigned to an imported route. If this object is not configured, the value will be 0.
hwIsisImportTag.name: hwIsisImportTag

hwIsisInterfaceIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface index.
hwIsisInterfaceIndex.name: hwIsisInterfaceIndex

hwIsisIntfBaseEntry.description: Each row defines some commands to a single interface of the IS-IS protocol existing on the system.
hwIsisIntfBaseEntry.name: hwIsisIntfBaseEntry

hwIsisIntfBaseTable.description: Set of commands on interface of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.
hwIsisIntfBaseTable.name: hwIsisIntfBaseTable

hwIsisIntfBfdEntry.description: Entry of BFD commands on interface of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.
hwIsisIntfBfdEntry.name: hwIsisIntfBfdEntry

hwIsisIntfBfdTable.description: Set of BFD commands on interface of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.
hwIsisIntfBfdTable.name: hwIsisIntfBfdTable

hwIsisIntfExtEntry.description: Entry of Some specific commands on interface of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system, which are different of IP type.
hwIsisIntfExtEntry.name: hwIsisIntfExtEntry

hwIsisIntfExtTable.description: Set of some specific commands on interface of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system, which are different of IP type.
hwIsisIntfExtTable.name: hwIsisIntfExtTable

hwIsisIntfRowStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the setting of two values: createAndGo(4): creates one row. destroy(6): deletes one row.
hwIsisIntfRowStatus.name: hwIsisIntfRowStatus

hwIsisIpTypeIndex.description: This object indicates the IP protocol type: ipv4(1): indicates IPv4. ipv6(2): indicates IPv6.
hwIsisIpTypeIndex.name: hwIsisIpTypeIndex

hwIsisL1CsnpTimerValue.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for sending Level-1 CSNP PDUs on an interface. The value ranges from 1 to 65535, in seconds. The default value is 10.
hwIsisL1CsnpTimerValue.name: hwIsisL1CsnpTimerValue

hwIsisL1ImportRouteExceedLimit.description: ISIS level-1 number of imported routes has exceeded the maximum limit.
hwIsisL1ImportRouteExceedLimit.name: hwIsisL1ImportRouteExceedLimit

hwIsisL1ImportRouteRestoreToLimit.description: ISIS level-1 number of imported routes is restored to less than or equal to the maximum limit.
hwIsisL1ImportRouteRestoreToLimit.name: hwIsisL1ImportRouteRestoreToLimit

hwIsisL1ImportRouteThresholdReach.description: ISIS level-1 number of imported routes has reached the threshold value.
hwIsisL1ImportRouteThresholdReach.name: hwIsisL1ImportRouteThresholdReach

hwIsisL1ImportRouteThresholdReachClear.description: ISIS level-1 number of imported routes has been less than the threshold value.
hwIsisL1ImportRouteThresholdReachClear.name: hwIsisL1ImportRouteThresholdReachClear

hwIsisL1TagValue.description: The value of this object identifies the tag value of a Level-1 interface. The value ranges from 0 to 4294967295. By default, it is 0, which indicates that the set tag value is deleted.
hwIsisL1TagValue.name: hwIsisL1TagValue

hwIsisL2CsnpTimerValue.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for sending Level-2 CSNP PDUs on an interface. The value ranges from 1 to 65535, in seconds. The default value is 10.
hwIsisL2CsnpTimerValue.name: hwIsisL2CsnpTimerValue

hwIsisL2ImportRouteExceedLimit.description: ISIS level-2 number of imported routes has exceeded the maximum limit.
hwIsisL2ImportRouteExceedLimit.name: hwIsisL2ImportRouteExceedLimit

hwIsisL2ImportRouteRestoreToLimit.description: ISIS level-2 number of imported routes is restored to less than or equal to the maximum limit.
hwIsisL2ImportRouteRestoreToLimit.name: hwIsisL2ImportRouteRestoreToLimit

hwIsisL2ImportRouteThresholdReach.description: ISIS level-2 number of imported routes has reached the threshold value.
hwIsisL2ImportRouteThresholdReach.name: hwIsisL2ImportRouteThresholdReach

hwIsisL2ImportRouteThresholdReachClear.description: ISIS level-2 number of imported routes has been less than the threshold value.
hwIsisL2ImportRouteThresholdReachClear.name: hwIsisL2ImportRouteThresholdReachClear

hwIsisL2TagValue.description: The value of this object identifies the tag value of a Level-2 interface. The value ranges from 0 to 4294967295. By default, it is 0, which indicates that the set tag value is deleted.
hwIsisL2TagValue.name: hwIsisL2TagValue

hwIsisLsdbThresholdReach.description: The number of LSP has reached the upper threshold value.
hwIsisLsdbThresholdReach.name: hwIsisLsdbThresholdReach

hwIsisLsdbThresholdReachClear.description: The number of LSP has been less than the lower threshold value.
hwIsisLsdbThresholdReachClear.name: hwIsisLsdbThresholdReachClear

hwIsisLspThrottleCount.description: The value of this object identifies the number of a bundle of LSPs. The value ranges from 1 to 1000. By default, it is 10.
hwIsisLspThrottleCount.name: hwIsisLspThrottleCount

hwIsisLspThrottleInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for sending batch of LSPs or CSNPs on an interface. The value ranges from 1 to 10000, in milliseconds. By default, the value is 50.
hwIsisLspThrottleInterval.name: hwIsisLspThrottleInterval

hwIsisMTIdIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the MT ID.
hwIsisMTIdIndex.name: hwIsisMTIdIndex

hwIsisMTName.description: This object indicates the name of the topology to be bound to an IS-IS process. The value is a string of 1 to 31 characters.
hwIsisMTName.name: hwIsisMTName

hwIsisModuleFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities implementing the Huawei ISIS MIB
hwIsisModuleFullCompliance.name: hwIsisModuleFullCompliance

hwIsisNETEntry.description: Each row means one network entity of the process.
hwIsisNETEntry.name: hwIsisNETEntry

hwIsisNETIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the NET index. It is a string of 8 to 20 bytes.
hwIsisNETIndex.name: hwIsisNETIndex

hwIsisNETStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the status of the NET table. createAndGo(4): A row is created. destroy(6): A row is deleted.
hwIsisNETStatus.name: hwIsisNETStatus

hwIsisNETTable.description: Set of network entities of process.
hwIsisNETTable.name: hwIsisNETTable

hwIsisOwnSysID.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually.
hwIsisOwnSysID.name: hwIsisOwnSysID

hwIsisPrefixPriorityEntry.description: Entry of priority-based convergence, each entry means one priority-based command for IS-IS process.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityEntry.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityEntry

hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1IpPrefixName.description: This object indicates the name of a Level-1 IP prefix policy. The name is a string of 0 to 169 characters. Zero-length means no configuration.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1IpPrefixName.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1IpPrefixName

hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1PolicyType.description: This object indicates the type of a Level-1 route preference policy: none(0): indicates that no policy type is specified. prefix(1): indicates the IP prefix policy. tag(2): indicates the administrative tag policy.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1PolicyType.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1PolicyType

hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1TagValue.description: This object indicates the administrative tag of the Level-1 route preference.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1TagValue.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityL1TagValue

hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2IpPrefixName.description: This object indicates the name of a Level-2 IP prefix policy. The name is a string of 0 to 169 characters. Zero-length means no configuration.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2IpPrefixName.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2IpPrefixName

hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2PolicyType.description: This object indicates the type of a Level-2 route preference policy: none(0): indicates that no policy type is specified. prefix(1): indicates the IP prefix policy. tag(2): indicates the administrative tag policy.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2PolicyType.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2PolicyType

hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2TagValue.description: This object indicates the administrative tag of the Level-2 route preference.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2TagValue.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityL2TagValue

hwIsisPrefixPriorityTable.description: Set of commands of priority-based convergence.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityTable.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityTable

hwIsisPrefixPriorityTypeIndex.description: This object indicates the preference of a route: medium(1): indicates medium. high(2): indicates high. critical(3): indicates critical.
hwIsisPrefixPriorityTypeIndex.name: hwIsisPrefixPriorityTypeIndex

hwIsisProcAreaAuthCode.description: The value of this object identifies the code of area authentication. none (0): The authentication code is not configured. osi (10): indicates OSI authentication. ip (133): indicates IP authentication.
hwIsisProcAreaAuthCode.name: hwIsisProcAreaAuthCode

hwIsisProcAreaAuthKeychainName.description: This object indicates the keychain name of IS-IS area authentication. The name is a string of characters. The name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that no IS-IS area authentication keychain name is configured. When read, it returns the keychain name.
hwIsisProcAreaAuthKeychainName.name: hwIsisProcAreaAuthKeychainName

hwIsisProcAreaAuthPacketAuthMode.description: The value of this object identifies the packet authentication mode of IS-IS area authentication: none (0): Authentication mode is not configured. authenticateall (1): Encapsulates authentication information for both transmitted and received LSPs and SNPs. allsendonly (2): Encapsulates authentication information for both generated LSPs and SNPs; does not authenticate received LSPs or SNPs. snppacketauthenticationavoid (3): Encapsulates authentication information for only generated LSPs and authenticates received LSPs. snppacketsendonly (4): Encapsulates authentication information for generated LSPs and SNPs; authenticates only received LSPs but does not authenticate received SNPs. By default, authentication is not configured.
hwIsisProcAreaAuthPacketAuthMode.name: hwIsisProcAreaAuthPacketAuthMode

hwIsisProcAreaAuthPasswordName.description: This object indicates the password of IS-IS area authentication. The password is a string of characters. If the IS-IS area authentication mode is simple, the password is a string of 0 to 16 characters. If the IS-IS area authentication mode is MD5, the password is a string of 0 to 392 characters. If the IS-IS area authentication mode is keychain, the name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that no IS-IS area authentication password is configured. When read, it always returns length 0.
hwIsisProcAreaAuthPasswordName.name: hwIsisProcAreaAuthPasswordName

hwIsisProcAreaAuthType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of IS-IS area authentication. null (0): Area authentication is not configured. md5 (1): The password is sent after being encrypted through MD5. simple (2): The password is sent in the form of simple text. keychain (3): The key chain table that changes with time is sent after being encrypted through MD5. By default, area authentication is not configured.
hwIsisProcAreaAuthType.name: hwIsisProcAreaAuthType

hwIsisProcAutoCostEnabled.description: This object indicates whether automatic interface cost calculation is enabled: true(1): indicates that automatic interface cost calculation is enabled. false(2): indicates that automatic interface cost calculation is disabled. By default, automatic interface cost calculation is disabled.
hwIsisProcAutoCostEnabled.name: hwIsisProcAutoCostEnabled

hwIsisProcBFDEnabled.description: Whether to enable BFD on each interface. true (1): enables BFD on each interface. false (2): does not enable BFD on each interface. By default, BFD is disabled on each interface.
hwIsisProcBFDEnabled.name: hwIsisProcBFDEnabled

hwIsisProcBFDFrrBindEnabled.description: Enables BFD-FRR binding on each interface. true (1): enables BFD-FRR binding on each interface. false (2): does not enable BFD-FRR binding on each interface. By default, BFD-FRR binding is disabled on each interface.
hwIsisProcBFDFrrBindEnabled.name: hwIsisProcBFDFrrBindEnabled

hwIsisProcBFDMinRecvInteval.description: The value of this object identifies the minimum interval for receiving BFD packets. If isis binding to vpn and ipv4-family not enable, The value is zero.
hwIsisProcBFDMinRecvInteval.name: hwIsisProcBFDMinRecvInteval

hwIsisProcBFDMinTxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the minimum interval for sending BFD packets. If isis binding to vpn and ipv4-family not enable, The value is zero.
hwIsisProcBFDMinTxInterval.name: hwIsisProcBFDMinTxInterval

hwIsisProcBFDMultiplier.description: The value of this object identifies the local detection multiplier. The value ranges from 1 to 255. If isis binding to vpn and ipv4-family not enable, The value is zero.
hwIsisProcBFDMultiplier.name: hwIsisProcBFDMultiplier

hwIsisProcBandWidthReference.description: This object is used to set the reference bandwidth.
hwIsisProcBandWidthReference.name: hwIsisProcBandWidthReference

hwIsisProcBaseEntry.description: Each row defines some commmands to a single process of the IS-IS protocol existing on the system. These commands belong to the IS-IS process.
hwIsisProcBaseEntry.name: hwIsisProcBaseEntry

hwIsisProcBaseTable.description: The set of commands of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.
hwIsisProcBaseTable.name: hwIsisProcBaseTable

hwIsisProcCostStyle.description: Configures the cost type of the IS-IS process: narrow (1): the narrow type narrowcompatible (2): the narrow-compatible type compatible (3): compatible type wide (4): wide type widecompatible (5): wide-compatible type narrowcompatiblerelax (6): narrow-compatible relax-spf-limit type compatible-relax (7): compatible relax-spf-limit type By default, the cost type of an IS-IS process is narrow.
hwIsisProcCostStyle.name: hwIsisProcCostStyle

hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvAvoidLearnEnabled.description: This object indicates whether an IS-IS process is prevented from learning default routes or adding them to the routing table: true(1): indicates that an IS-IS process is prevented from learning default routes or adding them to the routing table. false(2): indicates that an IS-IS process can learn default routes and then add them to the routing table. By default, an IS-IS process can learn default routes and then add them to the routing table.
hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvAvoidLearnEnabled.name: hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvAvoidLearnEnabled

hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvCost.description: This object is used to set the cost of a default route.
hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvCost.name: hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvCost

hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvLevel.description: This object is used to set the level of a default route: level1(1): indicates Level-1. level2(2): indicates Level-2. level12(3): indicates Level-1-2. By default, the level of a default route is Level-2.
hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvLevel.name: hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvLevel

hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvPolicyName.description: This object indicates the routing policy name. The name is a string of 0 to 40 characters.
hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvPolicyName.name: hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvPolicyName

hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvTag.description: This object is used to set the administrative tag of a default route.
hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvTag.name: hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvTag

hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvType.description: This object is used to set the mode in which default routes are advertised: null(0): indicates that default routes are not advertised. always(1): indicates that default routes are always advertised. matchdefault(2): If there is the default route that is generated by another routing protocol or another IS-IS process in the routing table, this default route is advertised in an LSP. If this default route is deleted from the routing table, this default route is not advertised in the LSP. routepolicy(3): indicates that default routes are advertised according to the routing policy.
hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvType.name: hwIsisProcDefRoutAdvType

hwIsisProcDomainAuthCode.description: The value of this object identifies the code of domain authentication. none (0): The authentication code is not configured. osi (10): indicates OSI authentication. ip (133): indicates IP authentication.
hwIsisProcDomainAuthCode.name: hwIsisProcDomainAuthCode

hwIsisProcDomainAuthKeychainName.description: This object indicates the keychain name of IS-IS domain authentication. The name is a string of characters. The name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that no IS-IS domain authentication keychain name is configured. When read, it returns the keychain name.
hwIsisProcDomainAuthKeychainName.name: hwIsisProcDomainAuthKeychainName

hwIsisProcDomainAuthPacketAuthMode.description: The value of this object identifies the packet authentication mode of IS-IS route domain authentication. none (0): Authentication mode is not configured. authenticateall (1): Encapsulates authentication information for both transmitted and received LSPs and SNPs. allsendonly (2): Encapsulates authentication information for both generated LSPs and SNPs; does not authenticate received LSPs or SNPs. snppacketauthenticationavoid (3): Encapsulates authentication information for only generated LSPs and authenticates received LSPs. snppacketsendonly (4): Encapsulates authentication information for generated LSPs and SNPs; authenticates only received LSPs but does not authenticate received SNPs. By default, authentication is not configured.
hwIsisProcDomainAuthPacketAuthMode.name: hwIsisProcDomainAuthPacketAuthMode

hwIsisProcDomainAuthPasswordName.description: This object indicates the password of IS-IS routing domain authentication. The password is a string of characters. If the IS-IS routing domain authentication mode is simple, the password is a string of 0 to 16 characters. If the IS-IS routing domain authentication mode is MD5, the password is a string of 0 to 392 characters. If the IS-IS routing domain authentication mode is keychain, the name is a string of 0 to 47 characters. The length 0 indicates that the password of IS-IS routing domain authentication is not configured. When read, it always returns length 0.
hwIsisProcDomainAuthPasswordName.name: hwIsisProcDomainAuthPasswordName

hwIsisProcDomainAuthType.description: The value of this object identifies the type of IS-IS router domain authentication. null (0): Domain authentication is not configured. md5 (1): The password is sent after being encrypted through MD5. simple (2): The password is sent in the form of simple text. keychain (3): The key chain table that changes with time is sent after being encrypted through MD5. By default, IS-IS route domain authentication is disabled.
hwIsisProcDomainAuthType.name: hwIsisProcDomainAuthType

hwIsisProcDynamicName.description: Configures the name of the IS-IS dynamic host. The value is a string of 1 to 64 characters. When the length is 0, the configured IS-IS dynamic host name is deleted.
hwIsisProcDynamicName.name: hwIsisProcDynamicName

hwIsisProcGREnabled.description: Whether to enable IS-IS GR. true (1): enables IS-IS GR. false (2): does not enable IS-IS GR. By default, IS-IS GR is disabled.
hwIsisProcGREnabled.name: hwIsisProcGREnabled

hwIsisProcGRInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum intervals for enabling GR. The value ranges from 0 to 1800, in seconds. By default, the value is 300 seconds. The value 0 indicates that GR is not configured.
hwIsisProcGRInterval.name: hwIsisProcGRInterval

hwIsisProcGRSuppresSAEnabled.description: This object indicates that the SA bit in the sent Hello packet is set to 1 after the GR-enabled device is started: true (1): enables this function. false (2): disables this function. By default, IS-IS does not suppress Hello PDUs from carrying SA bits.
hwIsisProcGRSuppresSAEnabled.name: hwIsisProcGRSuppresSAEnabled

hwIsisProcIPv6EnableTopologyType.description: This objects indicates whether the IPv6 topology is enabled for the IS-IS process: disable(0): disables the IPv6 topology of the IS-IS process. standard(1): specifies the topology type as the standard mode. ipv6(2): enables IPv6 for the IS-IS process in the IPv6 topology. compatible(3): specifies the topology type as the compatible mode. compatibleenablemtspf(4): indicates that SPF calculation is performed in the IPv6 topology in compatible mode. By default, the IPv6 topology is not enabled for the IS-IS process.
hwIsisProcIPv6EnableTopologyType.name: hwIsisProcIPv6EnableTopologyType

hwIsisProcIdIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the IS-IS process ID. The value ranges from 1 to 65535.
hwIsisProcIdIndex.name: hwIsisProcIdIndex

hwIsisProcL1CircuitCost.description: Global level-1 cost for all the interfaces. If the costStyle of the process is wide or widecompatible, the range of this value is from 1 to 16777215, else the range of this value is from 1 to 63.
hwIsisProcL1CircuitCost.name: hwIsisProcL1CircuitCost

hwIsisProcL1CircuitDefaultTag.description: This object is used to set the default administrative tag of an IS-IS Level-1 route.
hwIsisProcL1CircuitDefaultTag.name: hwIsisProcL1CircuitDefaultTag

hwIsisProcL1FlashFloodCount.description: The value of this object identifies the counter of level-1 LSPs on the interface. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 15. The value 0 indicates that no counter is configured. The default value is 5.
hwIsisProcL1FlashFloodCount.name: hwIsisProcL1FlashFloodCount

hwIsisProcL1FlashFloodInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the intervals for level-1 LSP flooding. The value ranges from 10 to 50000, in milliseconds. The default value is 10 ms.
hwIsisProcL1FlashFloodInterval.name: hwIsisProcL1FlashFloodInterval

hwIsisProcL1LowerRedistThreshold.description: This object is used to set the lower threshold value of level-1 import limit. The value range is from 1 to 100. The default means 70.
hwIsisProcL1LowerRedistThreshold.name: hwIsisProcL1LowerRedistThreshold

hwIsisProcL1RedistMaxLimit.description: This object is used to set the maximum limit number of IS-IS Level-1 redistribute routes advertised in LSPs. The value range is from 0 to 10000000. The default value 0 means no limit.
hwIsisProcL1RedistMaxLimit.name: hwIsisProcL1RedistMaxLimit

hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenIncrInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the delay timer for generating two level-1 LSPs with the same LSP ID. The value ranges from 1 to 60000, in milliseconds. By default, the value is 0.
hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenIncrInterval.name: hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenIncrInterval

hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenInitInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the delay timer that initially triggers a level-1 LSP. The value ranges from 0 to 60000, in milliseconds. By default, the value is 0.
hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenInitInterval.name: hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenInitInterval

hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenMaxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the timer for the maximum delay of level-1 LSPs with the same LSP ID. The value ranges from 1 to 120, in seconds. By default, the value is 2s.
hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenMaxInterval.name: hwIsisProcL1TimerLspGenMaxInterval

hwIsisProcL1TotalRedist.description: This object is used to get the number of level-1 import routes.
hwIsisProcL1TotalRedist.name: hwIsisProcL1TotalRedist

hwIsisProcL1UpperRedistThreshold.description: This object is used to set the upper threshold value of level-1 import limit. The value range is from 1 to 100. The default means 80.
hwIsisProcL1UpperRedistThreshold.name: hwIsisProcL1UpperRedistThreshold

hwIsisProcL2CircuitCost.description: Global level-2 cost for all the interfaces. If the costStyle of the process is wide or widecompatible, the range of this value is from 1 to 16777215, else the range of this value is from 1 to 63.
hwIsisProcL2CircuitCost.name: hwIsisProcL2CircuitCost

hwIsisProcL2CircuitDefaultTag.description: This object is used to set the default administrative tag of an IS-IS Level-2 route.
hwIsisProcL2CircuitDefaultTag.name: hwIsisProcL2CircuitDefaultTag

hwIsisProcL2FlashFloodCount.description: The value of this object identifies the counter of level-2 LSPs on the interface. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 15. The value 0 indicates that no counter is configured. The default value is 5.
hwIsisProcL2FlashFloodCount.name: hwIsisProcL2FlashFloodCount

hwIsisProcL2FlashFloodInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the intervals for level-2 LSP flooding. The value ranges from 10 to 50000 in milliseconds. The default value is 10ms.
hwIsisProcL2FlashFloodInterval.name: hwIsisProcL2FlashFloodInterval

hwIsisProcL2LowerRedistThreshold.description: This object is used to set the lower threshold value of level-2 import limit. The value range is from 1 to 100 The default means 70.
hwIsisProcL2LowerRedistThreshold.name: hwIsisProcL2LowerRedistThreshold

hwIsisProcL2RedistMaxLimit.description: This object is used to set the maximum limit number of IS-IS Level-2 redistribute routes advertised in LSPs. The value range is from 0 to 10000000. The default value 0 means no limit.
hwIsisProcL2RedistMaxLimit.name: hwIsisProcL2RedistMaxLimit

hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenIncrInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the delay timer for generating two Level-2 LSPs with the same LSP ID. The value ranges from 1 to 60000, in milliseconds. By default, the value is 0.
hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenIncrInterval.name: hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenIncrInterval

hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenInitInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the delay timer that initially triggers a Level-2 LSP. The value ranges from 1 to 60000, in milliseconds. By default, the value is 0.
hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenInitInterval.name: hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenInitInterval

hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenMaxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the timer for the maximum delay of Level-2 LSPs with the same LSP ID. The value ranges from 1 to 120, in seconds. By default, the value is 2s.
hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenMaxInterval.name: hwIsisProcL2TimerLspGenMaxInterval

hwIsisProcL2TotalRedist.description: This object is used to get the number of level-2 import routes.
hwIsisProcL2TotalRedist.name: hwIsisProcL2TotalRedist

hwIsisProcL2UpperRedistThreshold.description: This object is used to set the upper threshold value of level-2 import limit. The value range is from 1 to 100. The default means 80.
hwIsisProcL2UpperRedistThreshold.name: hwIsisProcL2UpperRedistThreshold

hwIsisProcLevel.description: The value of this object identifies the level of the IS-IS process. level1 (1): indicates level 1. level2 (2): indicates level 2. level12 (3): indicates level 1-2. By default, the level of an IS-IS process is level-1-2.
hwIsisProcLevel.name: hwIsisProcLevel

hwIsisProcLogPeerChange.description: Generates a log when the status of the peer changes. null (0): not configured enabledwithouttopology (1): IPv4 topology enabledwithtopology (2): IPv6 topology
hwIsisProcLogPeerChange.name: hwIsisProcLogPeerChange

hwIsisProcLsdbLowerThreshold.description: This object is used to set the lower threshold value of LSPs limit. The value range is from 1 to 100. The default means 70.
hwIsisProcLsdbLowerThreshold.name: hwIsisProcLsdbLowerThreshold

hwIsisProcLsdbTotal.description: This object is used to get the number of IS-IS LSPs.
hwIsisProcLsdbTotal.name: hwIsisProcLsdbTotal

hwIsisProcLsdbUpperThreshold.description: This object is used to set the upper threshold value of LSPs limit. The value range is from 1 to 100. The default means 80.
hwIsisProcLsdbUpperThreshold.name: hwIsisProcLsdbUpperThreshold

hwIsisProcMTExtEntry.description: Each row defines some commands specific to a single process of the IS-IS protocol existing on the system. These commands are different from ProcBaseTable for IP type and MT.
hwIsisProcMTExtEntry.name: hwIsisProcMTExtEntry

hwIsisProcMTExtTable.description: Set of commands of the integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system, which are different for IP type and MT.
hwIsisProcMTExtTable.name: hwIsisProcMTExtTable

hwIsisProcMTStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table: createAndGo(4): indicates that a row is created. destroy(6): indicates that a row is deleted.
hwIsisProcMTStatus.name: hwIsisProcMTStatus

hwIsisProcMaxLoadBalance.description: This object is used to set the number of equal-cost routes. The range and the default value depend on license. If isis binding to vpn and ip-family not enable, The value is zero.
hwIsisProcMaxLoadBalance.name: hwIsisProcMaxLoadBalance

hwIsisProcOnStartFromPeerInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum interval for waiting to clear the overload bit after the system is started and the neighbor relationship is established. The value ranges of set is from 5 to 86400, in seconds. The default value is 1200s. 0 means no configuration.
hwIsisProcOnStartFromPeerInterval.name: hwIsisProcOnStartFromPeerInterval

hwIsisProcOnStartInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the interval for waiting to clear the overload bit after the system is started. The value ranges from 5 to 86400, in seconds. The default value is 600s.
hwIsisProcOnStartInterval.name: hwIsisProcOnStartInterval

hwIsisProcOnStartStartFromPeer.description: This object indicates the system ID of a neighbor.
hwIsisProcOnStartStartFromPeer.name: hwIsisProcOnStartStartFromPeer

hwIsisProcOnStartWaitForBgpEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the function of waiting for BGP convergence is enabled: true(1): indicates that the function of waiting for BGP convergence is enabled. false(2): indicates that the function of waiting for BGP convergence is disabled. By default, the function of waiting for BGP convergence is disabled.
hwIsisProcOnStartWaitForBgpEnabled.name: hwIsisProcOnStartWaitForBgpEnabled

hwIsisProcOptionalChecksumEnabled.description: Enables BFD-FRR binding on each interface. true (1): enables optional checksum for CSNP,PSNP and IIH PDU. false (2): disables optional checksum for CSNP,PSNP and IIH PDU. By default, optional checksum is disabled.
hwIsisProcOptionalChecksumEnabled.name: hwIsisProcOptionalChecksumEnabled

hwIsisProcPrefPolicyName.description: This object indicates the name of the routing policy used for route filtering. The name is a string of 0 to 40 characters. Zero-length means no configuration.
hwIsisProcPrefPolicyName.name: hwIsisProcPrefPolicyName

hwIsisProcPrefValue.description: This object is used to set the preference of an IS-IS route. The value ranges from 1 to 255, and the default value is 15. If isis binding to vpn and ip-family not enable, The value is zero.
hwIsisProcPrefValue.name: hwIsisProcPrefValue

hwIsisProcRowStatus.description: This object supports settings of two values. createAndGo(4): A row is created. destroy(6): A row is deleted.
hwIsisProcRowStatus.name: hwIsisProcRowStatus

hwIsisProcSetOverLoad.description: This object indicates whether a device is enabled to notify its neighbors that its status is Overload: disable (0): indicates that a device is disabled from notifying its neighbors that its status is Overload. enable(1): indicates that a device is enabled to notify its neighbors that its status is Overload. onstartup(2): When a device is restarted or becomes faulty, it notifies its neighbors that its status is Overload.
hwIsisProcSetOverLoad.name: hwIsisProcSetOverLoad

hwIsisProcSetOverLoadAllowRoute.description: This object indicates that the type of routes to be advertised when a device is in the Overload state: null(0): indicates that no route type is specified. external(1): indicates the imported external routes. interlevel(2): indicates the leak routes. externalandinterlevel(3): indicates the imported external and leak routes.
hwIsisProcSetOverLoadAllowRoute.name: hwIsisProcSetOverLoadAllowRoute

hwIsisProcTEEnableLevel.description: Enables IS-IS TE. none (0): does not enable IS-IS TE. level1 (1): enables level-1 TE. level2 (2): enables level-2 TE. level12 (3): enables level-1-2 TE. By default, IS-IS TE is disabled.
hwIsisProcTEEnableLevel.name: hwIsisProcTEEnableLevel

hwIsisProcTimerMaxAge.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum Keepalive time of the LSP. The value ranges from 2 to 65535, in seconds. The default value is 1200s.
hwIsisProcTimerMaxAge.name: hwIsisProcTimerMaxAge

hwIsisProcTimerRefresh.description: The value of this object identifies the timer of LSP refreshing. The value ranges from 1 to 65534, in seconds. The default value is 900s.
hwIsisProcTimerRefresh.name: hwIsisProcTimerRefresh

hwIsisProcTimerSPFIncrInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the incremental delay timer for two SPF calculations. The value ranges from 1 to 60000, in milliseconds. By default, the interval is 200ms.
hwIsisProcTimerSPFIncrInterval.name: hwIsisProcTimerSPFIncrInterval

hwIsisProcTimerSPFInitInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the delay timer for initial SPF calculation. The value ranges from 1 to 60000, in milliseconds. By default, the interval is 50ms.
hwIsisProcTimerSPFInitInterval.name: hwIsisProcTimerSPFInitInterval

hwIsisProcTimerSPFMaxInterval.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum intervals for SPF calculation. The value ranges from 1 to 120, in seconds. By default, the value is 5s.
hwIsisProcTimerSPFMaxInterval.name: hwIsisProcTimerSPFMaxInterval

hwIsisProcVpn6Name.description: The value of this object identifies the name of the IPv6 VPN instance bound to the IS-IS process. The value ranges from 0 to 31.
hwIsisProcVpn6Name.name: hwIsisProcVpn6Name

hwIsisProcVpnName.description: The value of this object identifies the name of the IPv4 VPN instance bound to the IS-IS process. The value ranges from 0 to 31.
hwIsisProcVpnName.name: hwIsisProcVpnName

hwIsisRemoteIP.description: IP address of the remote end.
hwIsisRemoteIP.name: hwIsisRemoteIP

hwIsisRouteLeakFilterPolicyBasicAcl.description: The value of this object identifies the number of a basic ACL. The value ranges from 2000 to 2999. 0 means no configuration, The range of this value is from 2000 to 2999.
hwIsisRouteLeakFilterPolicyBasicAcl.name: hwIsisRouteLeakFilterPolicyBasicAcl

hwIsisRouteLeakFilterPolicyPolicyName.description: The policy name of route leak. If policy type is aclName, the length of this value is from 1 to 32.
